[[!tag lang:en FrankZappa blogging history]]

Frank Zappa used to say that he viewed some of his work as
journalism: reporting what he saw around him in society. Thus, if
historians from the future want to learn more about our society,
looking at rock songs might be a good start.

Well, now we have the web, and with blogging, we’ve got way better
materials for historians in the future. Although, as usual, the
biggest challenge here is that most of the links from 2001
blogging don’t work any more. Most of the time, professional
editors and big companies are usually better in [keeping their
URI cool][coolURI].

[coolURI]: http://www.w3.org/Provider/Style/URI.html "Cool URIs don’t change"

